\frac{dx}{cy-bz}=\frac{dy}{az-cx}=\frac{dz}{bx-ay}
P=cy-bz
Q=az-cx
R=bx-ay
P'=a
Q'=b
R'=c
PP'+QQ'+RR'=0
c_1=ax+by+cz
\frac{xdx+ydy}{cxy-bxz+ayz-cxy}=\frac{dz}{bx-ay}
\frac{xdx+ydy}{z(ay-bx)}=\frac{dz}{-(ay-bx)}
c_2=x^2+y^2+z^2
\Delta=(ab)^2-(c^2-a^2)(c^2-b^2)=c^2[a^2+b^2-c^2]>0
c<\sqrt{a^2+b^2}
(c^2-a^2)x^2+(c^2-b^2)y^2+2abxy-2c_1(ax+by)=c^2c_2-c_1^2
